<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Weapon Card</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Mono&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: 'Roboto Mono', monospace;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        min-height: 100vh;
        background-color: #f0f0f0;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 20px;
      }

      .card {
        width: 400px;
        border: 1px solid #000;
        background-color: #f0f0f0;
        box-shadow: 5px 5px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
      }

      .header {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 10px;
        font-size: 0.9em;
        align-items: start;
      }
      .header .left-header{
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;

      }
      .header .weapon-name{
        font-size: 1.2em;
      }

      .header .right-header {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 10px;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }


      .image {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 20px;
      }

      .image img {
        max-width: 100%;
        height: auto;
      }

      .stats {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
        padding: 10px;
        font-size: 0.9em;

      }

      .description {
        padding: 10px;
        text-align: justify;
        font-size: 0.8em;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }
       @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .card {
            width: 95%;
        }
        .header {
            flex-direction: column; /* Stack header elements on smaller screens */
        }
        .header .right-header{
          grid-template-columns: 1fr ;
        }

        .stats {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr; /* Stack stats on smaller screens */
        }
    }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="card">
        <div class="header">
            <div class = "left-header">
                <div class="weapon-name">.44 Pistol</div>
                <div class="details">Small Guns .44 Magnum</div>
            </div>
            <div class = "right-header">
                <div class="cost">
                    <div>Cost</div>
                    <div>99</div>
                </div>
                <div class="weight">
                    <div>Weight</div>
                    <div>4</div>
                    <div>lbs</div>
                </div>
                <div class="rarity">
                    <div>Rarity</div>
                    <div>2</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="image">
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/300x150?text=.44+Pistol" alt=".44 Pistol" />
        </div>
        <div class="stats">
            <div class="damage">
                <div>Damage Dice</div>
                <div>6</div>
                <div>Physical</div>
            </div>
            <div class="rate">
                <div>Fire Rate</div>
                <div>1</div>
            </div>
            <div class="range">
                <div>Range</div>
                <div>C</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
            <p>
                Close Quarters: A Close Quarters weapon is easy to use up-close, and suffers no difficulty increase for being
                used when within Reach of an enemy.
            </p>
            <p>
                Vicious: The attack inflicts +1 damage for each Effect
                rolled.
            </p>
            <p>
                The .44 pistol is a double-action revolver,
                chambered to use the .44 Magnum cartridge. It's a
                powerful gun, though not as customizable as other
                handguns. Due to their simple, rugged design,
                they're prized by their owners, but not so
                uncommon as to be truly rare.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
